 The car involved was completely mangled, offering little to no resistance against the heavy duty truck. Traffic was brought to a stand still after the collision with very little answers as to what led to the tragedy.  A witness at the scene, told www.mobserver.co.za that two occupants of the Nissan were involved in the accident as well as thetruck driver. It is unclear to the extent of what their injuries were. He confirmed that the accident occured on Thursday afternoon around 14:00 and that police were on the scene.   R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za